    "description": "Manufactured OpenAPI artifact for Nextech Select Practice APIs. This file was synthesized by Last Mile from curated research JSON and is not vendor-certified. Use it as an agent-consumable starting point, then validate paths, schemas, authentication, and server URLs with the vendor before production use. Nextech documents its Select APIs as a RESTful implementation based on the FHIR standard, with supported functionality for patient demographics, clinical information, patient creation and updates, payment posting, appointment information, appointment confirmation, appointment booking, slot information, non-clinical patient notes, and patient-document attachment. The public docs and downloadable R4 OpenAPI file also cover resources such as Encounter, Device, DiagnosticReport, DocumentReference, Claim, PaymentReconciliation, Location, Practitioner, Slot, and patient-recall. This is a robust write-capable healthcare integration surface, but it is not an asset or telemetry API. Asset data is Unsupported. Telemetry data is Unsupported. Writeback is Supported.",
